  "description": [
    "Friday September 12 1941 Soviet Union Giant Among Nations Has Vast Human and Natural Resources In attacking the Soviet Union the Germans have challenged the worlds largest nation points out a bulletin from the National Geographic Society The Soviet Union including the territories of Poland the three Baltic countries and Bessarabia occupied since the autumn of 1939 has an area between two and a half and three times the size of continental United States It has a population of more than 193000000 people To worldtraveler Humboldt Rus sia was a land as big as the face of the moon It takes 11 hours for the sun to cross it ten days for the traveler to go by rail from Moscow to Vladivostok Streehing from Hie Baltic to the Pacific from the Atlantic Ocean to the Black Sea the Soviet Union in cludes more than 175 different racial groups speaking almost as many lan guages and dialects It is master in Europe and Asia of an enormous trea sure chest of natural resources many of which have already been tapped Soviet authorities estimate their coal deposits at more than one and u half trillion tons or 21 per cent of the"
